main event: A large silver object with four lights in the middle was spotted moving at a high rate of speed near Pasadena, California on October 5, 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as having a bright white fluorescent appearance.
The object was traveling northward at an estimated speed of 2,300 mph with slight maneuvers.
The object was sighted by two children at an altitude of around 5,000 feet.
The location indicates the object was likely an aircraft climbing on a northwesterly heading from a Los Angeles airport.
The report notes that there was usual commercial and military air traffic in the Los Angeles area at the time.
sighted object: A large silver disc-shaped object with four lights in the middle
